Prototype scope creates a new bean instance every time it is requested from the container.

10.What is the Java Memory Model (JMM)?
The Java Memory Model (JMM) defines how threads interact with memory in a concurrent Java application. It specifies the rules for how changes made by one thread to shared variables are guaranteed to be visible to other threads.


