What is the use of serialversion uuid ?
In Java, the serialVersionUID is a unique identifier for a serializable class. The primary purpose of serialVersionUID is to ensure that the serialized form of a class is compatible between different versions of that class.

Difference between Comparable and Comparator?
Comparable is used to define the natural/default sorting of a class. It provides the compareTo() method and the sorting logic is written inside the class itself. Only one sorting rule can be defined.
Comparator is used to define custom or multiple sorting orders. It provides the compare() method and the sorting logic is written in a separate class, so you can create multiple comparators without modifying the original class.
